1
00:00:01,730 --> 00:00:06,860
<b><i>Thirteen ancient wands
are said to exist in the Magic Realm.</i></b>

2
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:12,610
<b><i>The wands choose only those
with innate talents</i></b>

3
00:00:13,820 --> 00:00:18,660
<b><i>and bestow blessings upon their wielders.</i></b>

4
00:00:19,910 --> 00:00:23,750
<b><i>These wands are called the Master Canes.</i></b>

5
00:01:57,420 --> 00:02:02,430
<b><i>The qualifying round for the Divine Visionary
Candidate Exam, "The Life Crystal."</i></b>

6
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:08,020
<b><i>Each team has three members, and they strive
to break the crystals of opposing teams.</i></b>

7
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:09,850
<b><i>However...</i></b>

8
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,400
<b>It's...</b>

9
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:15,650
<b>It's a team match.
So why are we forced to split apart!?</b>

10
00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:19,660
<b>Damn it!</b>

11
00:02:20,530 --> 00:02:21,950
<b>What a problem.</b>

12
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:23,410
<b>I have to go find Finn.</b>

13
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:27,040
<b>Are we totally screwed now?</b>

14
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:29,540
<b>I gotta find him real fast.</b>

15
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:36,960
<b><i>I'm sure they're in bad shape right now.</i></b>

16
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:43,550
<b><i>Crap, crap, crap.</i></b>

17
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:47,520
<b><i>Mash and Dot don't have
their crystals anymore.</i></b>

18
00:02:49,980 --> 00:02:52,310
<b><i>This is the one crystal we have left.</i></b>

19
00:02:52,650 --> 00:02:55,190
<b><i>I have to guard it with my life.</i></b>

20
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,320
<b>I-I'm sorry.</b>

21
00:03:03,490 --> 00:03:06,540
<b>Please forgive me!</b>

22
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,710
<b><i>Carpaccio.</i></b>

23
00:03:13,170 --> 00:03:15,590
<b><i>There's a knife in his shoulder.</i></b>

24
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:22,340
<b>Our birth decides
who can climb to the peak.</b>

25
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:27,350
<b>Talent is not distributed evenly.</b>

26
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:38,480
<b>That's why you need to live the life
you were made for.</b>

27
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:41,610
<b>Got that, weakling?</b>

28
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:47,120
<b><i>He's worse than bad news to go that far!</i></b>

29
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:49,500
<b><i>If I were to run into him now...</i></b>

30
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,750
<b><i>He's on the move.</i></b>

31
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:58,340
<b><i>Will he catch on
because I made noise while running?</i></b>

32
00:03:59,210 --> 00:04:02,170
<b><i>I have to lay low here.</i></b>

33
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:06,510
<b><i>All right. I need to sever
my presence as organic matter.</i></b>

34
00:04:06,970 --> 00:04:09,430
<b><i>I am a wall. Stay away.</i></b>

35
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,770
<b><i>I am a wall. Stay away.</i></b>

36
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:15,520
<b><i>I am a wall. I'm a wall. I'm a...</i></b>

37
00:04:27,070 --> 00:04:30,540
<b><i>He's gone. I successfully became a wall.</i></b>

38
00:04:31,910 --> 00:04:33,290
<b>What are you doing?</b>

39
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,790
<b>I am a wall.</b>

40
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,970
<b>You're funny.</b>

41
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:49,220
<b><i>H-Help me!</i></b>

42
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,890
<b>Please. I'll lick your shoes.
I'll even lick between your toes.</b>

43
00:04:52,890 --> 00:04:54,230
<b>Please help me!</b>

44
00:04:54,730 --> 00:04:57,480
<b>You... You're Finn Ames.</b>

45
00:04:57,690 --> 00:04:59,400
<b><i>Huh? How does he know me?</i></b>

46
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,230
<b>The continuing student
who barely made the cutoff.</b>

47
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:05,490
<b><i>I've become famous in the worst way!</i></b>

48
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:07,700
<b>I remember you well.</b>

49
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:11,200
<b>I was wondering
how someone like this is at Easton.</b>

50
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:15,160
<b>And yet, here you are
at the Divine Visionary Candidate Exam.</b>

51
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:17,960
<b>Did your brother get you in?</b>

52
00:05:18,130 --> 00:05:24,800
<b>I feel nothing but dissatisfaction
when I see talentless trash like you.</b>

53
00:05:25,670 --> 00:05:32,010
<b>Give me that crystal.
It's not suitable for the likes of you.</b>

54
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:35,390
<b>Hurry up and hand it over.</b>

55
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,400
<b><i>He's so scary!
This is totally intimidating.</i></b>

56
00:05:40,150 --> 00:05:41,150
<b><i>But...</i></b>

57
00:05:41,770 --> 00:05:45,070
<b><i>this crystal holds Mash's future.</i></b>

58
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:48,780
<b><i>The choice I need to make...</i></b>

59
00:05:49,530 --> 00:05:51,080
<b><i>Protect this crystal to the...</i></b>

60
00:05:57,410 --> 00:05:59,330
<b><i>Why am I suddenly bleeding?</i></b>

61
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:01,130
<b><i>Magic?</i></b>

62
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:03,590
<b>What did you just try to do?</b>

63
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:07,420
<b>You're weak but acting like a big shot.</b>

64
00:06:07,590 --> 00:06:10,590
<b>I'm asking you.
What did you just try to do?</b>

65
00:06:11,350 --> 00:06:17,020
<b><i>Oh, this is that distinct feeling
I get when I'm truly terrified.</i></b>

66
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:22,860
<b><i>My blood vessels are squeezed shut,
and my heart is clamped down by a cold chill.</i></b>

67
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:26,900
<b>Surely you're aware
of the difference in our abilities.</b>

68
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,950
<b>You're going to lose that crystal anyway.</b>

69
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:35,580
<b>Be submissive and had it over.
It's better to not feel any pain.</b>

70
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:38,540
<b>You don't want to end up like that, do you?</b>

71
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:43,090
<b>I won't say it again.</b>

72
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:47,340
<b>Now, give it up.</b>

73
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,110
<b><i>I'd say we've got
three standouts in this exam.</i></b>

74
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:07,780
<b><i>Mash Burnedead, who can't use magic.</i></b>

75
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:12,870
<b><i>Lance Crown, the top transfer student.</i></b>

76
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:14,620
<b><i>And...</i></b>

77
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:19,750
<b><i>Carpaccio Luo-yang,
the top continuing student.</i></b>

78
00:07:20,790 --> 00:07:22,500
<b><i>But I always imagined he was like me</i></b>

79
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:26,300
<b><i>with no interest
in becoming a Divine Visionary.</i></b>

80
00:07:27,170 --> 00:07:32,380
<b><i>I'd guess Orter Madl cut him a deal,
like he did with me.</i></b>

81
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:37,350
<b><i>Carpaccio is a prodigy, chosen by
a wand fit to be a national treasure.</i></b>

82
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:42,690
<b><i>It's not an exaggeration to say
he's the most talented in our academy.</i></b>

83
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:47,730
<b><i>Not quite mature. An unripe fruit.</i></b>

84
00:07:47,900 --> 00:07:49,530
<b><i>Blessings from the earth...</i></b>

85
00:07:50,780 --> 00:07:53,360
<b><i>My gratitude to all living creatures...</i></b>

86
00:07:53,660 --> 00:07:59,040
<b><i>And Daddy and Mommy, thank you
for bringing me into this world.</i></b>

87
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:04,170
<b>I don't get it.</b>

88
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:08,670
<b>That crystal will end up as mine anyway.</b>

89
00:08:10,550 --> 00:08:12,090
<b><i>Don't give up.</i></b>

90
00:08:12,590 --> 00:08:16,550
<b><i>If I can protect this crystal
during this showdown...</i></b>

91
00:08:17,050 --> 00:08:20,430
<b><i>Now is my chance,
as he's totally underestimating me.</i></b>

92
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:24,520
<b><i>I haven't used my personal magic yet.</i></b>

93
00:08:24,850 --> 00:08:26,400
<b><i>That's what I'm betting on.</i></b>

94
00:08:26,610 --> 00:08:27,650
<b>Dangerousse!</b>

95
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,160
<b><i>Nothing is happening?</i></b>

96
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,330
<b><i>A lie so he could escape.</i></b>

97
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,500
<b><i>I can catch up soon enough.</i></b>

98
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:47,920
<b>Changeas!</b>

99
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:55,130
<b><i>This is where I crushed the first crystal.</i></b>

100
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:58,890
<b><i>The student I beat earlier is gone.</i></b>

101
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:01,890
<b><i>Magic that switches locations.</i></b>

102
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:08,400
<b><i>The reason Finn didn't use his magic
until now was to catch me off guard?</i></b>

103
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:11,860
<b><i>All right. I gained quite a bit of distance.</i></b>

104
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:15,150
<b><i>It was the right decision to save
my personal magic till the end.</i></b>

105
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:16,410
<b><i>I'll make my escape...</i></b>

106
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:20,160
<b><i>What? My leg...</i></b>

107
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:25,040
<b><i>It hurts... Damn it...</i></b>

108
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,290
<b><i>Footsteps?</i></b>

109
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,340
<b><i>This is bad.</i></b>

110
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:36,260
<b>Is this your last-ditch effort?</b>

111
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:39,600
<b>You already understand, don't you?</b>

112
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:42,310
<b>The difference between you and me!</b>

113
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:46,310
<b>Now, give it here.</b>

114
00:09:53,070 --> 00:09:57,280
<b>Weakling. You need to step down.</b>

115
00:10:00,450 --> 00:10:03,990
<b>What is that magic? He transfers damage?</b>

116
00:10:04,410 --> 00:10:07,080
<b>That's going way too far.</b>

117
00:10:12,290 --> 00:10:13,500
<b>Enough alre—</b>

118
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:14,670
<b>No...</b>

119
00:10:16,050 --> 00:10:18,970
<b>I will not give this to you.</b>

120
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:21,600
<b><i>But I really am glad.</i></b>

121
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,270
<b><i>To have a great guy like you for a friend.</i></b>

122
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,100
<b>Even if I'm a loser...</b>

123
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:31,230
<b>Even if I'm a coward...</b>

124
00:10:31,730 --> 00:10:33,360
<b><i>Let's come back again sometime.</i></b>

125
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,360
<b>I can't do it.</b>

126
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:41,700
<b>I can't do something as pathetic
as abandoning my friend!</b>

127
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:44,950
<b>Nalcos!</b>

128
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,160
<b>Nalco—</b>

129
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:52,880
<b>That's enough. How abominable.</b>

130
00:10:56,300 --> 00:11:01,640
<b>Incompetent people who make
an effort irritate me the most.</b>

131
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:08,230
<b>I will show you
that all your efforts are in vain.</b>

132
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:13,520
<b>Hey, this is looking bad.
If he cuts his neck...</b>

133
00:11:16,530 --> 00:11:18,320
<b><i>I will not...</i></b>

134
00:11:18,820 --> 00:11:22,570
<b>- Stop.
- If he keeps going, it'll kill him.</b>

135
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:28,450
<b><i>No matter what, I will not...</i></b>

136
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:42,760
<b>It wasn't in vain.</b>

137
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:44,760
<b>Because I'm here now.</b>

138
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,270
<b>Finn...</b>

139
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,690
<b>Thank you.</b>

140
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:54,480
<b>Mash.</b>

141
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:02,030
<b>Mash.</b>

142
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,780
<b>Sorry I'm so late.</b>

143
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:08,790
<b>Huh?</b>

144
00:12:09,580 --> 00:12:10,750
<b>What does this mean?</b>

145
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:21,260
<b>I'm incapable of feeling pain.</b>

146
00:12:22,550 --> 00:12:23,880
<b>What's that?</b>

147
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:28,390
<b>My wand is special.</b>

148
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,230
<b>What nonsense are you talking...</b>

149
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:44,070
<b><i>Mash's attacks are reflecting back at him?</i></b>

150
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:50,080
<b>My magic transfers damage I take
back to my opponent.</b>

151
00:12:50,540 --> 00:12:53,250
<b>So if I get hurt...</b>

152
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:56,750
<b>Mash!</b>

153
00:13:02,170 --> 00:13:03,880
<b><i>His wounds healed?</i></b>

154
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:10,310
<b>On the other hand, all pain I suffer
is absorbed by this wand.</b>

155
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,390
<b>I don't control it.</b>

156
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:14,690
<b>The inability to be hurt</b>

157
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:20,190
<b>is the blessing of the Master Cane,
the most ancient of wands.</b>

158
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:25,650
<b>This power was automatically activated
the moment it chose me.</b>

159
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:31,830
<b>Thus, from the moment I was born,
I've never felt any pain.</b>

160
00:13:34,620 --> 00:13:38,790
<b><i>The most ancient of wands,
of which there are only 13.</i></b>

161
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:42,300
<b><i>He's making full use of a Master Cane.</i></b>

162
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:46,720
<b><i>Bona fide talent
acknowledged as a chosen one.</i></b>

163
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:50,180
<b><i>We sure have a good crop
of first-years this year.</i></b>

164
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:53,680
<b>I would like to feel pain.</b>

165
00:13:54,560 --> 00:14:00,150
<b>But someone of your caliber
is a far cry from dealing pain to me.</b>

166
00:14:00,770 --> 00:14:02,690
<b>Let's hurry up and end this.</b>

167
00:14:07,950 --> 00:14:10,950
<b><i>He stabs himself
to damage his opponent.</i></b>

168
00:14:10,950 --> 00:14:12,950
<b><i>It's an unavoidable attack.</i></b>

169
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:23,000
<b>That's useless.
No attack can give me any pain.</b>

170
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:35,060
<b><i>It's no good. All the damage
is reflected back to Mash.</i></b>

171
00:14:35,430 --> 00:14:38,980
<b><i>It's like Carpaccio
is always on the offense!</i></b>

172
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:43,070
<b><i>You can't even call this a fight.</i></b>

173
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,190
<b>This is a farce.</b>

174
00:14:46,690 --> 00:14:51,200
<b>A person's fate is determined
by the abilities they are born with.</b>

175
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:55,040
<b>What you're doing now
is for self-satisfaction.</b>

176
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:57,330
<b>Completely useless.</b>

177
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,460
<b>The same can be said
for Finn Ames over there.</b>

178
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,880
<b>A loser from back in middle school.</b>

179
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:07,460
<b>Always compared to his brother,
but always on the verge of flunking.</b>

180
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:09,970
<b>He's out of place to begin with.</b>

181
00:15:10,130 --> 00:15:12,890
<b>People like him don't belong here.</b>

182
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:18,100
<b>He can't even protect
a single crystal on his own.</b>

183
00:15:18,310 --> 00:15:21,020
<b>He's a weakling,
always being saved by others...</b>

184
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:24,480
<b>You're an eyesore, Finn.</b>

185
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,320
<b>You have a point.</b>

186
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:34,200
<b><i>It's wiser to quit something
if you can't do it.</i></b>

187
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:38,750
<b><i>And it's important to look at yourself
objectively so you can know your place.</i></b>

188
00:15:39,580 --> 00:15:44,590
<b>Finn's actions in your eyes
may be futile efforts,</b>

189
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,880
<b>and he may be an eyesore.</b>

190
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:51,050
<b>But...</b>

191
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:54,090
<b>desperately standing against
something you fear...</b>

192
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:59,730
<b>My friend is standing against someone
overwhelmingly stronger than himself.</b>

193
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,020
<b>And to thoughtlessly laugh
and look down on him...</b>

194
00:16:04,310 --> 00:16:05,940
<b>I won't allow that.</b>

195
00:16:09,190 --> 00:16:10,530
<b>Mash.</b>

196
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:21,790
<b><i>Consecutive attacks?</i></b>

197
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:25,130
<b><i>If Mash incurs any further damage...</i></b>

198
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:29,130
<b><i>Consecutive attacks
so the healing speed can't keep up.</i></b>

199
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:33,630
<b><i>Useless. Such a simple tactic
to attempt to break through.</i></b>

200
00:16:34,130 --> 00:16:36,640
<b><i>I had the slightest bit
of expectation from him.</i></b>

201
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:38,390
<b><i>But what a shame.</i></b>

202
00:16:40,140 --> 00:16:42,390
<b><i>What? A crack in the Goddess Statue?</i></b>

203
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:50,650
<b><i>Did the Goddess Statue
actually have a capacity limit?</i></b>

204
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,400
<b><i>Impossible.</i></b>

205
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:55,660
<b><i>This has never happened before.</i></b>

206
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:06,250
<b>Of course, I'm a million times
stronger than you are.</b>

207
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:13,800
<b>But when you realize that, can you
stand against me like Finn stood against you?</b>

208
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:16,680
<b>Mash.</b>

209
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:20,680
<b><i>What kind of body does this guy have?</i></b>

210
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:22,220
<b><i>Damn him.</i></b>

211
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:29,440
<b><i>This is the first time someone
cracked the Goddess Statue.</i></b>

212
00:17:31,570 --> 00:17:34,490
<b><i>But the Goddess Statue
triggers automatically.</i></b>

213
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:39,870
<b><i>It simply becomes more defensive
the more attacks I withstand.</i></b>

214
00:17:56,050 --> 00:17:58,390
<b>I won't kill you right away.</b>

215
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:01,850
<b><i>I feel elated...</i></b>

216
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:05,480
<b><i>to the fact that such a human existed.</i></b>

217
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:08,480
<b><i>In this world, where everything...</i></b>

218
00:18:08,940 --> 00:18:10,730
<b><i>is nothing but a haze.</i></b>

219
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:22,540
<b><i>An iron wand?</i></b>

220
00:18:36,590 --> 00:18:37,970
<b>No way!</b>

221
00:18:38,130 --> 00:18:41,300
<b>He's sculpting the iron wand
with the strength of his fingers?</b>

222
00:18:41,430 --> 00:18:44,810
<b>BAM</b>

223
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,810
<b>He made a tennis racket!?</b>

224
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:14,590
<b><i>He's dodging the syringes
while targeting repeated shots</i></b>

225
00:19:15,210 --> 00:19:17,380
<b><i>at that one crack
in the Goddess Statue!?</i></b>

226
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:24,930
<b><i>Is he...</i></b>

227
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:27,930
<b><i>playing wall rally with that nurse?</i></b>

228
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,290
<b><i>Impossible.</i></b>

229
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:57,000
<b>If you want to know that badly,
I'll teach you.</b>

230
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:01,220
<b>FWIP FWIP</b>

231
00:19:59,470 --> 00:20:01,220
<b>What pain is.</b>

232
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,600
<b><i>Wasn't that a bit excessive?</i></b>

233
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:16,020
<b>Come on, you're kidding me.</b>

234
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:18,110
<b>Is that even possible?</b>

235
00:20:18,730 --> 00:20:22,110
<b>Carpaccio, a savant
chosen by a Master Cane.</b>

236
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:25,780
<b>He was just defeated by something
similar to wall-hitting tennis!</b>

237
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:31,370
<b>A decisive victory
against a Master Cane user.</b>

238
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,880
<b>Um, Mash...</b>

239
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:38,800
<b>I'm sorry, it's my fault.</b>

240
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,170
<b>Thank you.</b>

241
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:45,930
<b>I'm a klutz, and I always trouble others.</b>

242
00:20:47,390 --> 00:20:50,770
<b>But I can still stay together
with everyone thanks to you.</b>

243
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:53,140
<b>Thank you.</b>

244
00:20:58,610 --> 00:21:00,860
<b>Yeah. I'm glad.</b>

245
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:08,830
<b><i>So this is pain...</i></b>

246
00:21:09,410 --> 00:21:11,160
<b><i>I can't stop bleeding...</i></b>

247
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:16,420
<b><i>And the pain spreads with each heartbeat.</i></b>

248
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:19,920
<b><i>It hurts... It hurts...</i></b>

249
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:28,300
<b><i>So pain is something...
this horrifying, huh?</i></b>

250
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:31,180
<b><i>Such a...</i></b>

251
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:37,480
<b><i>He withstood this much pain
for someone else?</i></b>

252
00:21:38,690 --> 00:21:40,070
<b>Are you okay?</b>

253
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,230
<b>Yeah.</b>

254
00:21:41,230 --> 00:21:42,440
<b>Thank you.</b>

255
00:21:45,650 --> 00:21:51,200
<b><i>But when you realize that,
can you stand against me like Finn did?</i></b>

256
00:21:54,620 --> 00:21:57,880
<b>Indeed, the difference is obvious.</b>

257
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:02,170
<b>I was utterly outmatched.</b>

